+# LayerShellQt is Wayland-only (its one real use, desktopwindow.cpp's
+# desktop-background layer-shell setup, is already runtime-guarded behind
+# Application::underWayland() -- see this project's own libfm-qt
+# XCB-optional patch for the identical shape of fix). PureUnix has neither
+# X11 nor Wayland, so this is never buildable here at all; optional.
+find_package(LayerShellQt ${SHELLQT_MINIMUM_VERSION})
+# XCB isn't find_package()-d by upstream pcmanfm-qt at all (real desktop
+# Linux systems already have libxcb on the system linker path via Qt's own
+# xcb QPA plugin dependency chain) -- desktopwindow.cpp's one real XCB use
+# (setting the EWMH _NET_WM_WINDOW_TYPE_DESKTOP hint) is already
+# runtime-guarded behind `QGuiApplication::platformName() == "xcb"`, same
+# shape as libfm-qt's own XCB-optional patch. Added here explicitly since
+# PureUnix has no system XCB at all to implicitly link against.
+find_package(XCB)
 
